SIMPLE: infiltration
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Infiltration
<hw>In`fil*tra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>infiltration</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process of infiltrating, as of water into
a porous substance, of a fluid into the cells of an organ or part of the
body, or of persons into a hostile organization.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The substance which has entered the pores or
cavities of a body.</def> <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Calcareous <qex>infiltrations</qex> filling the cavities.</q>
<rj><qau>Kirwan.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fatty infiltration</b></col>. <fld>(Med.)</fld> <cd>See
under <er>Fatty</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Infiltration gallery</b></col>,
<cd>a filter gallery.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infiltrative</ent>⟦br⟧
